Flexible Income Evaluation 
Do not use fixed numeric income thresholds.
Income Interpretation Rule
Do not infer an income range unless the income certificate explicitly provides a range.
If the certificate states a single numeric value (e.g., ₹2,40,000 or ₹2.4 lakh), treat it as an exact amount — do not expand it into a higher range.
Do not guess or assume a larger income unless the documents clearly indicate it.
Instead, use reasoned judgment based on:
Family size (smaller vs. larger households)
Type of income source (if mentioned)
Language tone in the certificate (e.g., “below poverty line,” “low-income,” “moderate income,” etc.)
Consider family size
Income tone (e.g., “low-income,” “moderate,” “financial hardship”)
Whether income is proportionate to dependents
Whether income source suggests stability or instability
Example:
 
 ₹7 lakh for a family of 7 is inadequate →will be Green
 ₹7 lakh for a family of  3 is acceptable → likely Amber/Green


